ing effector cells such as natural killer cells, and complement dependent cytotoxicity is mediated by the FC region of the antibody binding to and inducing complement protein activity.[A7935,A7936,A7937]', 'Daratumumab is a monoclonal antibody that targets and induces apoptosis in cells that highly express CD38, including multiple myeloma cells.[L13290,L13296] It has a long duration of action as it is given every 1-4 weeks.[L13290,L13296] Patients should be counselled regarding the risk of hypersensitivity, neutropenia, thrombocytopenia, embryo-fetal toxicity, and interferences with cross-matching and red blood cell antibody screening.[L13290,L13296]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
