methylation is much less sensitive to fluconazole inhibition. Sertaconazole exhibits <i>in vitro</i> activity against <i>Cryptococcus neoformans</i> and <i>Candida spp.</i> Fungistatic activity has also been demonstrated in normal and immunocompromised animal models for systemic and intracranial fungal infections due to <i>Cryptococcus neoformans</i> and for systemic infections due to Candida albicans.', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
